The United States strongly condemns the terrorist attacks that took place in Kabul and Balkh Province, Afghanistan. These attacks targeted Shia civilians preparing for the Ashura holy day of mourning and were intended to create sectarian tension in the country. At least 32 people were killed and more than 80 were injured. The Afghan police and other security forces responded bravely to these attacks, and the United States fully supports efforts to bring the perpetrators to justice. The United States stands with the people and Government of Afghanistan in their efforts to build a more secure, stable, and prosperous country.